15.jpg","caption":"Flights halted across Gulf, wealthy travellers spend up to ₹2 Crore to fly out","sizes":{"16x9":{"url":"https://images.news18.com/ibnlive/uploads/2025/12/Untitled-design-2025-12-31T172230.644-2025-12-7db0776f923f70f7b340004b56fd7415-16x9.jpg"},"4x3":{"url":"https://images.news18.com/ibnlive/uploads/2025/12/Untitled-design-2025-12-31T172230.644-2025-12-7db0776f923f70f7b340004b56fd7415-4x3.jpg"},"3x2":{"url":"https://images.news18.com/ibnlive/uploads/2025/12/Untitled-design-2025-12-31T172230.644-2025-12-7db0776f923f70f7b340004b56fd7415-3x2.jpg"}}},"app_first":0,"has_video":false},{"story_id":9940667,"section":"lifestyle_news","headline":"Why Indians Bathe In The Morning While Chinese And Japanese Wait Until Night","created_at":"2026-03-04 08:10:11","updated_at":"2026-03-04 08:10:11","weburl":"https://www.news18.com/lifestyle/health-and-fitness/why-indians-bathe-in-the-morning-while-chinese-and-japanese-wait-until-night-ws-el-9940667.html","weburl_r":"/lifestyle/health-and-fitness/why-indians-bathe-in-the-morning-while-chinese-and-japanese-wait-until-night-ws-el-9940667.html","images":{"url":"https://images.news18.com/ibnlive/uploads/2026/03/image-2026-03-b4c1b375a3fe1d21c72e179c606f9af4-1200x800.jpg","caption":"Indians traditionally bathe in the morning for energy and health, while Chinese, Japanese, and Koreans prefer night baths to relax and cleanse after the day. (AI Generated)","alt":"Indians traditionally bathe in the morning for energy and health, while Chinese, Japanese, and Koreans prefer night baths to relax and cleanse after the day. (AI Generated)"},"intro":"For centuries, Indians have bathed in the morning for health and energy. But in neighbouring Asian countries, people bathe at night. So which time is truly best?","display_headline":"Why Indians Bathe In The Morning While Chinese And Japanese Wait Until Night","post_type":"text","liveblog_api_url":{"status":0,"title":"","blog_url":""},"categories":[{"id":339039,"name":"health and fitn